   <body>
      <context>
         <hazardstatement type="caution">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>HAZARD of injury or equipment damage</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>
                  <sl>
                     <sli>Mount the battery breaker box to a wall that is structurally
sound and able to support the weight of the unit.</sli>
                     <sli>Use appropriate mounting hardware and bolts that fit the wall
type.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <fig>
            <image href="../Images/pxc-bbb_mountthebox_w120mm_0000150885.svg"
                   scalefit="yes"
                   scope="local"
                   placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Measure and mark the four mounting hole locations on the
wall.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drill holes in each of the four marked locations.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Loosen the four screws on the front cover and remove the
front cover from the battery breaker box.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/pxc-bbb_removeinnercover_w120mm_0000150884.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Lift the battery breaker box, position it against the wall
and line it up with the four holes. Fasten with four M8 bolts (not
supplied).</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
